[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Troubleshooting reflection issues**\n\nI'm encountering some problems with setting access on private nested methods in Java, possibly due to Java 17's strong encapsulation. When using `getDeclaredMethod`, it returns accessible as false. I wonder if invoking it from a different package causes this issue. I think that if my search is successful, I won't need to call `setAccessible`. It seems that public methods from interfaces and superclasses are accessible, so that’s something to keep in mind.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0e3b13afa9f608260169f915c3958481959e6d855905bd2699\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-RXS4diyxKPOvqdlYdGzFm44IKQs0TLsTqqUpMw-5xlVRJ4uH1iIs07RhwPUQcuYHnoe8IQbGb4os0v5FMpOMV8mlZoBjQPPzYJ5BYJqj_rKmXhlbkmYCH6qhj0luXSjPYmyiNk6n5yHNEneNjlDg_c8stjWFT12BICS1E8A2Q7sdmebPH-_y0wZk7-dQ316kBlbjP7GV2ULKxe5CAPB0dog9XlGT4j5aOGpnbx11Y7q6K3bQOO7F6-3Cu_z-gdLq7MVrpEJSNvpDsAr1q3L78g-fTWzND5UsSm7Kl3po_kizBaCA4qalOGwJxx0TAi5xlJ4F38a1kC_3nszoVPyYGjTaO6gy0Ykr2BCzYK6qCPQxUGM6OuPJzIdnuiNHtXe_GKe4GN5hG5Q2aPGJG4Y2q-IdeZ9LvLePxPctb6wHAPfOuYc89mWu1R6r5ry_jwdJ1pDlbt380Q-kdCK74_3R7Rlo-NH3J87z42K7mV6BEIz-BXRtqIZj9jrqeRXmv8W1OLqCsYzYWPW5H4rOqrjvfxfwzQTJRiZ8KzosfKjsrEnBaSzXmSkEZskfrraJMXt3nKBem3dmUbbEqXc9Af11jr7Yn_i34uGEiQ3iF2z_Go29_37pTXY9avIuNCZOvW_4IMtxhX9bc6pMPK5teLsCNxxQsipS0cXm4gcHfxVyE11qBqz75c20bT2iACKd0WWMOM9SYDHWa_RnwqMWZ2TuiS1bJKCFTTfkUzrk0fYsw9-RxZGTMJx0rjQ92RNijY1ejYjPGDjGn5IvP5gZGMTNK7sU0sDrnFsuUK8VWoDf-Xle0vp7n8znHCoe5m-Mqx8X1cbgd9UGoiEBQATAmv0xEgRO5V2xwOMFvpNObYTngMoPh5oyRrI0UyCHg2q9PUb6c9HXTaj9lKjPZp8O7EJcn7M2fRv67PAiRsJ2uWxLgWrBU8I5c8XubhajGwUSsV0bmjuVOomvcxCs2qrNoCx2yD_EmjMARffiXfqFjw2uXujYLPO9kY39-zM_NJ4mZn_zA_rUZi2ngMF2O63VsfjeobfpsOY3zxu9zNn1O9Yir1bnXdEVBPNxbTDy1by4EFSIifboS8zRAS86mrlFFR9Jnn3oihwQ6GL0yZ4YTRa0CJbXvL8rk9OuYDw1clFPY26cSIpUjTf52BToGZQQAIQdco2PiHIxdabmab8zNjgwlrGUfIK6OILo9K88BnouSR5FttKvEdv4GlOUTNcNbf3XffgWAAuVQg