aPoWtJ4ShgPGPdpLCyxX2YVhrhx8kB6Z5QCyd\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Troubleshooting reflection issues**\\n\\nI'm encountering some problems with setting access on private nested methods in Java, possibly due to Java 17's strong encapsulation. When using `getDeclaredMethod`, it returns accessible as false. I wonder if invoking it from a different package causes this issue. I think that if my search is successful, I won't need to call `setAccessible`. It seems that public methods from interfaces and superclasses are accessible, so that’s something to keep in mind.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_oSQRGxiSMSaeZO4aGK5Z6anG|fc_0e3b13afa9f608260169f915d2bdb08195a83d68f6a7712773", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "../../source_context/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/main/extracted/rhino1_7R5/src/org/mozilla/javascript/FunctionObject.java", "offset": 135, "limit": 90}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 567, "output": 1127, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34462, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777931714365, "responseId": "resp_0e3b13afa9f608260169f915c2ce9c8195bcd5b01f019b29b4"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_oSQRGxiSMSaeZO4aGK5Z6anG|fc_0e3b13afa9f608260169f915d2bdb08195a83d68f6a7712773", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\n        if (member.isMethod()) {\n            Method method = member.method();\n            Class<?> returnType = method.getReturnType();\n            if (returnType == Void.TYPE) {\n                hasVoidReturn = true;\n            } else {\n                returnTypeTag = getTypeTag(returnType);\n            }\n        } else {\n            Class<?> ctorType = member.getDeclaringClass();\n            if (!ScriptRuntime.ScriptableClass.isAssignableFrom(ctorType)) {\n                throw Context.reportRuntimeError